liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Secretary of the Home Affairs Department, Mike Pezzullo, has been referred to the Australian Public Service Commissioner over text messages sent over a period of years to a Liberal Party power broker. Nine Newspapers has published a series of text messages sent between Mr Pezzullo and Liberal Party figure Scott Briggs. Many of the messages related to ministry appointments, including around the time Scott Morrison became Prime Minister. Home Affairs Minister Clare O'Neil has now referred the matter for consideration by the Public Service Commissioner, Gordon de Brouwer.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Mike Pezzullo referred to the Australian Public Service Commissioner over text messages

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Fresh off the back of four ARIA nominations, Kylie Minogue spoke to News Breakfast this morning about all things Padam Padam and her new album Tension. Australia's queen of pop is set to begin a three-month Vegas residency later this year and left the door open to a potential world tour in the future. " We're looking at these things, we're trying to make decisions. I'm trying to think of what to say right now!" Kylie said. "But I would love to tour. We're just trying to figure it out."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Kylie Minogue  tells News Breakfast she would 'love to tour'
